The paper proposes a proof technique for showing soundness of a predicate with respect to a big-step semantics. This involves defining constructions for an extended version of the big-step semantics, which is necessary for the meta-theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Logical Foundations of Computer Science (cs.LF), or Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories.
